Step.SQLStatement: CREATE OR REPLACE VIEW RV_FP_InvoiceLine AS SELECT il.AD_Client_ID, il.AD_Org_ID, il.Created, il.CreatedBy, il.Updated, il.UpdatedBy, il.IsActive, il.C_InvoiceLine_ID, il.C_Invoice_ID, il.C_Tax_ID, il.QtyInvoiced, il.PriceList AS PriceActual, p.Value, COALESCE(p.Name, c.Name, il.Description) AS Name, (ROUND((il.PriceList - il.PriceActual), 2) * il.QtyInvoiced) DiscountAmt FROM C_InvoiceLine il LEFT JOIN M_Product p ON(p.M_Product_ID = il.M_Product_ID) LEFT JOIN C_Charge c ON(c.C_Charge_ID = il.C_Charge_ID)

PO.Data: A Client is a company or a legal entity. You cannot share data between Clients. Tenant is a synonym for Client.
An organization is a unit of your client or legal entity - examples are store, department. You can share data between organizations.
The record is active in the system

There are two methods of making records unavailable in the system: One is to delete the record, the other is to de-activate the record. A de-activated record is not available for selection, but available for reports. There are two reasons for de-activating and not deleting records: (1) The system requires the record for audit purposes. (2) The record is referenced by other records. E.g., you cannot delete a Business Partner, if there are invoices for this partner record existing. You de-activate the Business Partner and prevent that this record is used for future entries.
The Created field indicates the date that this record was created.
The Updated field indicates the date that this record was updated.
The Created By field indicates the user who created this record.
The Updated By field indicates the user who updated this record.
The Tax indicates the type of tax used in document line.
The Invoiced Quantity indicates the quantity of a product that have been invoiced.
The Actual or Unit Price indicates the Price for a product in source currency.
Search key for the record in the format required - must be unique

A search key allows you a fast method of finding a particular record. If you leave the search key empty, the system automatically creates a numeric number. The document sequence used for this fallback number is defined in the "Maintain Sequence" window with the name "DocumentNo_<TableName>", where TableName is the actual name of the table (e.g. C_Order).
The name of an entity (record) is used as an default search option in addition to the search key. The name is up to 60 characters in length.
The Invoice Line uniquely identifies a single line of an Invoice.

Step.SQLStatement: CREATE OR REPLACE VIEW RV_FP_Invoice AS SELECT i.AD_Client_ID, i.AD_Org_ID, i.IsActive, i.CreatedBy, i.Created, i.Updated, i.UpdatedBy, i.C_Invoice_ID RV_FP_Invoice_ID, i.C_Invoice_ID, i.Description, u.Name AS SalesRep_Name, bp.TaxID, bp.Name, bp.Name2, c.Name AS CountryName, COALESCE(r.Name, l.RegionName) RegionName, COALESCE(ct.Name, City) AS City, l.Address1, l.Address2, l.Address3, l.Address4, i.Reversal_ID, da.FiscalDocumentNo AS ReversalDocumentNo, da.DateInvoiced AS ReversalDocumentDate, de.Value AS FiscalPrinterNo FROM C_Invoice i INNER JOIN C_BPartner bp ON(bp.C_BPartner_ID = i.C_BPartner_ID) INNER JOIN C_BPartner_Location bpl ON(bpl.C_BPartner_Location_ID = i.C_BPartner_Location_ID) INNER JOIN C_Location l ON(l.C_Location_ID = bpl.C_Location_ID) INNER JOIN C_Country c ON(c.C_Country_ID = l.C_Country_ID) LEFT JOIN C_Region r ON(r.C_Region_ID = l.C_Region_ID) LEFT JOIN C_City ct ON(ct.C_City_ID = l.C_City_ID) LEFT JOIN AD_User u ON(u.AD_User_ID = i.SalesRep_ID) LEFT JOIN C_Invoice da ON(da.C_Invoice_ID = i.Reversal_ID) LEFT JOIN AD_Device de ON(de.AD_Device_ID = da.AD_Device_ID)
